<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-65-1001 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author explains how to start a disarmament group. First, you needto get a few people together in your home to discuss how to form a groupin your community. Second, you need to call a public meeting with a goodspeaker who covers: the medical implications of nuclear war, the economicimplications of the arms race, the environmental impact, and the emotionalimpact of the arms race. Third, you need to get your message to the newsmedia. The author concludes that the only way to stop the arms race isfor each community to do its part.</TEXT></DOC>